node.text:
Staring contest. 🐅

Project C.A.T. has grown its commitment to tiger conservation, from initially supporting nearly 1M acres of tiger habitat in 2016 to now supporting nearly 6M acres. Thanks to these protections, tiger numbers have grown overall for the first time in a century.

Additionally, the project has provided resources to help restore 140 acres of grasslands in Bhutan in order to sustain tiger prey and enrich the landscape for other endangered species.
